<paragraph id="8B967449FFBFFFB07F95FC3B382CF9A9" blockId="8.[166,1225,794,1685]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
Diagnosis. Male imagoes reach 
<quantity id="4CD1D9ACFFBFFFB07D29FC3B399AFC08" box="[615,756,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2.2 mm</quantity>
in length. Eye bridge consists of 4 rows of ommatidia. Antennae are dense and long setosed, the bristles are slightly longer than a half of flagellomere width; flagellomere necks are dark. Length/width of 4th flagellomere is 4.0 (
<figureCitation id="131268CCFFBFFFB07FBDFC5B3A53FBA8" box="[243,317,1018,1044]" captionStart="Figs 32–38" captionStartId="7.[175,214,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[263,1143,864,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-325@7.[238,1168,851,1726]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 32–38. Corynoptera hypopygialis, male: 32 — thorax; 33 — ventral view of gonostyles; 34 — general view of hypopygium ventral; 35 — the fourth flagellomere; 36 — front tibial (t1) organ; 37 — helter; 38 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
fig. 
<emphasis id="B95DA85BFFBFFFB07E6FFC5B3A53FBA8" box="[289,317,1018,1044]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">35</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpus is short, bright colored, consists of 3 segments. Basal palpomere is a bit high-backed, with 1 long outer setae and indistinct sensory pit. Sensilla are long and curved. Palpomere 2 is the shortest, makes ¾ of basal one. Palpomere 3 approximately as long as basal one. Thorax and abdomen are strong and dark brown colored (
<figureCitation id="131268CCFFBFFFB07FA2FBDB3A59FB28" box="[236,311,1146,1172]" captionStart="Figs 32–38" captionStartId="7.[175,214,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[263,1143,864,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-325@7.[238,1168,851,1726]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 32–38. Corynoptera hypopygialis, male: 32 — thorax; 33 — ventral view of gonostyles; 34 — general view of hypopygium ventral; 35 — the fourth flagellomere; 36 — front tibial (t1) organ; 37 — helter; 38 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
fig. 
<emphasis id="B95DA85BFFBFFFB07E55FBDB3A59FB28" box="[283,311,1146,1172]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">32</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Postpronotum is bare; mesonotum with strong and dark setosity. Legs and gonocoxa are lighter than thorax, but noticeably dark. Tibial organ t1 with indistinct row of bristles (
<figureCitation id="131268CCFFBFFFB07E44FB1B3A3DFB68" box="[266,339,1210,1236]" captionStart="Figs 32–38" captionStartId="7.[175,214,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[263,1143,864,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-325@7.[238,1168,851,1726]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 32–38. Corynoptera hypopygialis, male: 32 — thorax; 33 — ventral view of gonostyles; 34 — general view of hypopygium ventral; 35 — the fourth flagellomere; 36 — front tibial (t1) organ; 37 — helter; 38 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
fig. 
<emphasis id="B95DA85BFFBFFFB07E79FB1B3A3DFB68" box="[311,339,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">36</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Tarsal claws without teeth. Wings are fumose, posterior veins and membrane without macrotrichia, 2.0– 
<quantity id="4CD1D9ACFFBFFFB07D7EFB7B39E5FB48" box="[560,651,1242,1268]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
in length; x is a bit shorter then y, bare or with 1–4 macrotrichia; r1 = r; r1 falls into C well before the base of M-fork; stM is longer than Mfork; stCu = ½–¼ x; c/w = 0.67 (
<figureCitation id="131268CCFFBFFFB07D6AFABB3900FA88" box="[548,622,1306,1332]" captionStart="Figs 32–38" captionStartId="7.[175,214,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[263,1143,864,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-325@7.[238,1168,851,1726]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 32–38. Corynoptera hypopygialis, male: 32 — thorax; 33 — ventral view of gonostyles; 34 — general view of hypopygium ventral; 35 — the fourth flagellomere; 36 — front tibial (t1) organ; 37 — helter; 38 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
fig. 
<emphasis id="B95DA85BFFBFFFB07D1CFABB3900FA88" box="[594,622,1306,1332]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">38</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Helter is shortened, dark brown colored (
<figureCitation id="131268CCFFBFFFB07B20FABB3FD6FA88" box="[1134,1208,1306,1332]" captionStart="Figs 32–38" captionStartId="7.[175,214,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[263,1143,864,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-325@7.[238,1168,851,1726]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 32–38. Corynoptera hypopygialis, male: 32 — thorax; 33 — ventral view of gonostyles; 34 — general view of hypopygium ventral; 35 — the fourth flagellomere; 36 — front tibial (t1) organ; 37 — helter; 38 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
fig. 
<emphasis id="B95DA85BFFBFFFB07BD2FABB3FD6FA88" box="[1180,1208,1306,1332]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">37</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Hypopygium is spherical, unicolorous dark brown and concolorous with the abdomen; gonocoxa with very long black bristles on the inner parts, without basal differentiation (
<figureCitation id="131268CCFFBFFFB07FE0FADB3B97FA28" box="[174,249,1402,1428]" captionStart="Figs 32–38" captionStartId="7.[175,214,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[263,1143,864,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-325@7.[238,1168,851,1726]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 32–38. Corynoptera hypopygialis, male: 32 — thorax; 33 — ventral view of gonostyles; 34 — general view of hypopygium ventral; 35 — the fourth flagellomere; 36 — front tibial (t1) organ; 37 — helter; 38 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
fig. 
<emphasis id="B95DA85BFFBFFFB07F93FADB3B97FA28" box="[221,249,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">34</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Gonostulus is bubble-thick, evenly rounded on the outside (
<figureCitation id="131268CCFFBFFFB07C95FADB3F48FA28" box="[987,1062,1402,1428]" captionStart="Figs 32–38" captionStartId="7.[175,214,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[263,1143,864,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-325@7.[238,1168,851,1726]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 32–38. Corynoptera hypopygialis, male: 32 — thorax; 33 — ventral view of gonostyles; 34 — general view of hypopygium ventral; 35 — the fourth flagellomere; 36 — front tibial (t1) organ; 37 — helter; 38 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
fig. 
<emphasis id="B95DA85BFFBFFFB07B44FADB3F48FA28" box="[1034,1062,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">33</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). The apex of gonostulus is tight and short setosed, with apical tooth and 4 megasetae (located per two pairs on the noticeable socket). Genital plate (tegmen) is larger in width than in height. Aedeagal teeth are small, with one-pointed apexes. Aedeagus is short, strong sclerotized (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB809B8FFBFFFB07FE0FA5B3AE9F9A8" author="Lengersdorf, F." box="[174,391,1530,1556]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" pagination="122 - 129" refId="ref6522" refString="Lengersdorf, F. 1926. Die Sciariden des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien. Konowia, 5 (2), 122 - 129." type="journal article" year="1926">Lengersdorf, 1926</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB809B8FFBFFFB07EDCFA5B3960F9A8" author="Frey, R." box="[402,526,1530,1556]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" pagination="33 - 112" refId="ref6221" refString="Frey, R. 1948. Entwurf einer neuen Klassifikation der Muckenfamilie Sciaridae (Lycoriidae). II Die nordeu 1 opaischen Arten. Notul. Ent., 27 (2 - 4), 33 - 112." type="journal article" year="1948">Frey, 1948</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB809B8FFBFFFB07D57FA5B3858F9A9" author="Menzel, F. &amp; Mohrig, W." box="[537,822,1530,1557]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" pagination="63 - 80" refId="ref6622" refString="Menzel, F., Mohrig, W. 1993. Beitrage zur Taxonomie und Faunistik der palaarktischen Trauermucken (Diptera, Sciaridae) Teil IV. Lengersdorf'sche Sciaridentypen aus dem Naturhistorischen Museum Wien (1. Beitrag). Beitr. Ent., 43 (1), 63 - 80." type="journal article" year="1993">Menzel &amp; Mohrig, 1993</bibRefCitation>
